I usually love this location, but last night really ruined it for me :( my boyfriend and I ordered our burgers as lettuce wraps. The cashier rudely said, "that's hardly a burger." Like okay? That commentary wasn't necessary. I asked if he needed a signature on the receipt because it had a signature line and he told me no like I was stupid. We got our receipt and our drink cup and went to sit down. The ice machine did not work. Our order took almost 20 minutes to come out when there was only one other group of two waiting for their food. So just to clarify, we ordered lettuce wraps and every time we've done this it comes as a burger wrapped in lettuce (obviously). This time it came in a tin box with one piece of lettuce. Our toppings were put on the bottom of the tin, underneath the burger. I ordered raw onions, but was given sautéed onions. We both asked for mayo on our burgers and it came on the side. It was incredibly hard to eat, the burgers were dry, and didn't have the right toppings. I've worked in both fast food and retail and I get that it can get hectic, but this was just sad. Rude cashier and getting our orders wrong was enough for me to not want to come here again. I'll will be going to the other Five Guys on Milwaukee from now on.
